To the Court, the Clerk of the Court, and to Defendant **Megan Nicole Bentley** and her counsel of record:

Plaintiff **Michael James Romero** ("Plaintiff") hereby applies **ex parte** for an **Order Shortening Time** on **Plaintiff's Motion to Compel Defendant's Deposition; Request for Monetary Sanctions; and Request for Limited Leave After Cutoff** (the "Motion") and for a condensed briefing schedule. Plaintiff does **not** seek a merits ruling at the ex parte appearance; the merits of the Motion will be heard and decided at the advanced hearing.

**Relief Requested (CRC 3.1201(1), 3.1300(b); CCP § 1005(b)).**
Plaintiff moves ex parte for an order: (1) shortening time and **advancing the hearing** on Plaintiff's Motion (currently set for **February 11, 2026 at 9:00 a.m.**) to the **earliest date available** to the Court **on or about Thursday, December 4, 2025**; and (2) setting a **condensed briefing schedule** (Opposition due **5 court days** before the advanced hearing; Reply due **2 court days** before), pursuant to **California Rules of Court ("CRC") 3.1200--3.1207 and 3.1300(b**, order shortening time) and **Code of Civil Procedure ("CCP") § 1005(b)** (court may prescribe a shorter time). Good cause is shown in the concurrently filed **Declaration of Michael James Romero (Urgency)** and **Declaration re Notice**, which are expressly incorporated here by reference. 

This Application is made pursuant to **CRC 3.1200--3.1207** (ex parte rules), **CRC 3.1300(b)** (order shortening time), **CRC 3.1201** (required documents), **CRC 3.1202** (contents of application), and **CCP § 1005(b)** (notice period and court's power to shorten time), on the grounds set forth below, in the supporting declarations, and in the underlying Motion.  

